9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 936, L.D. 1427, “An Act Extending the
10 Statute of Limitations on Criminal Actions Involving Aggravated Sex Trafficking”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in the last 2 lines (page 1, lines 11 and 12 in L.D.) by
12 striking out the following: "or for which the prosecution has not yet been barred by the
13 statute of limitations in force immediately prior to the effective date of this Act"
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, provides that the 20-
1188 year statute of limitations established in the bill applies only to those Class A or Class B
1199 crimes of aggravated sex trafficking committed on or after the effective date of this
2200 legislation.
